Patient received first dose of Pfizer covid-19 vaccine on 4/9/2021 at 1800 with her mother in attendance after consent was acquired. At 1805 patient began to feel hot and nauseous. The patient thought she was going to vomit, so she left her chair in the waiting area to head to the restroom at the back of the store. at 1807, Upon rising the patient became weak in the knees and began to collapse. The patient's mother initially supported the patient and I was called to assist the patient to the floor. The patient was very pale in appearance as she was assisted gently to the floor, avoiding any injury. EMS was called shortly after the event around 1810. The patient remained conscious however was a bit disoriented initially while lying on the floor. The patient recovered quickly, however remained nauseous and complained of feeling hot. Upon questioning the patient, she had not eaten since lunch at school at 1300. The patient was given a cold water and a sprite, of which she had a couple of drinks out of each. The patient was relocated back into a chair at 1815 as she was feeling much better. EMS arrived at 1821. EMS performed a general assessment and a blood pressure check resulting in 130/80. The patient's mother dismissed any further treatment from EMS. EMS exited the building at 1827. The patient and mother waited in the store for a while longer. Both patient and mother exited on their own, denying escort from associates at 1840.

Patient chronic conditions (JIA, UC) previously controlled on adalimumab. Within several days of receiving COVID-19 vaccine dose #2, patient began experiencing worsening/flare of ulcerative colitis symptoms including stomach pain, diarrhea, fatigue, arthritis pain that lasted beyond the reasonable and known duration of vaccine related side-effects. Symptoms treated with dicyclomine and acetaminophen with no relief. Symptoms continued x 2 weeks. Patient ultimately required addition of budesonide to treatment regimen for ulcerative colitis and is currently having relief of symptoms.
16 2021-05-12 limb discomfort The patient felt tired and describes her eyes going dark, then passed out a few minutes after vaccin... Read more
Close
The patient felt tired and describes her eyes going dark, then passed out a few minutes after vaccination. She was vaccinated and then left the immunization room to sit down for a 15 minute waiting period. When she went to sit down, she collapsed on the floor. Her mother assisted her into a chair. She continued to be incoherent and have her eyes rolling back into her head for a few minutes. We used a cool cloth on her forehead and the back of her neck. The parents requested that we call 911. EMS arrived shortly and evaluated her. Heart rate, blood pressure, pulse ox, blood sugar and chest sounds were all within normal range. The patient stated that her arm felt heavy and "funny". She then stated that her tongue felt funny. EMS evaluated her tongue and said it looked normal. To err on the side of caution, she was taken to the hospital to determine whether or not she was having a delayed onset anaphylactic reaction. This patient has no history of seizures.
16 2021-05-13 muscle pain 12 hours post vaccine she had severe myalgia, rash on both arms and legs, headache, nausea, stomach ... Read more
Close
12 hours post vaccine she had severe myalgia, rash on both arms and legs, headache, nausea, stomach pain, and mild swelling in legs. Over the next 48 hours the rash darkened and spread to the entire body causing pain in her skin. The myalgia became nearly unbearable and both Ibuprofen and Acetaminophen didn't put a dent in the pain. One side of her face swelled so that one eye could only partially open. The nausea and stomach pain worsened so that she couldn't eat. Headache became intense. By 48 hours post vaccine she became delirious - her speech was slurred and difficult to comprehend. She would fall asleep for a few minutes and wake up unaware of where she was or what was happening. She never got a fever but did have chills. Around this time I called a relative who is a doctor to seek advice and Diphenhydramine was recommended. Benedryl helped immensely. 30 minutes after taking it she could speak clearly, was more alert, pain became tolerable, and her appetite returned. Symptoms and swelling returned when the Benedryl wore off so she continued taking it every 4 hours for the next two days until it wasn't necessary any more. The myalgia, stomach pain and headache persisted for 7 days. At 8 days post vaccine (today) a mild headache, mild and intermittent stomach pain, and mild fatigue are her only remaining symptoms. Her pediatrician cannot see her until next week but we have an appt for the 22nd.

Close
At 2am 4/22 patient started to feel sick and sent a text that I didn't read until 630 as I was asleep. She had severe muscle aches, hurt to move, hurt to breathe and felt like she was having a heart attack. She felt like she might pass out and had some blurred vision. At 630am, I saw her texts and immediately brought her 2 tylenol and a large glass of water. She went back to bed. She woke up around 10:45 and was feeling decent except for a headache but no fever or anything so we went to try on some Prom dresses. At the dress shop, she collapsed and had a seizure lasting around a minute. She lost her bladder and was completely confused and incoherent. She's never had a seizure before. I scooped her up, brought her to the ER where they ran every test and scan imagineable. Full blood work up and cultures, a chest xray, a CT scan of her brain and lungs. Her temp was high 103-104 and she had full body chills and a pounding headache. Her BP kept dropping and got as low as 81/36. They threw 2 bags of IV fluids into her and admitted her to the hospital. She had also developed a heart murmur. Over the course of the night, her BP stabilized but her temp continued to spike and come back down with Tylenol/Ibuprofen. She also had IV Tordahl for the headache. Her inflammatory markers were high at 15.3 which we were told should be less than 1. They reran labs in the morning but everything can back really low which they felt was a dilution effect from all the fluids so wanted us to follow up with her primary care on Monday. On Saturday night, he lymph nodes were swollen to the size of ping pong balls but have since slowly reduced in size although still there. Her labs were better from discharge and her white blood cell count was within range and her inflammatory marker was down to 1.7. Her blood sugar was a little low. She did pass out and have seizure like response to giving blood in the doctors office, lost bladder control again, shot pupils, etc. She is still stuttering over words, has some short term memory retention and has some motor function issues which they think is a result of the initial seizure and should resolve itself over time. Her liver function tests were totally normal in the hospital but are a high now so they will be checking her out again next week.

However, these are the same symptoms I have whenever I am allergic to a medication, NSAIDS, dicyclomine, etc. It always starts with ascending numbness from my fingers to the rest of my body. Then I start to shake and my heart rate goes way up. Usually I start to cough then vomit and my airway closes. Thankfully this time we were able to slow the process and I never experienced some of the last symptoms.

The patient previously took the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; Lot number EL3246) on 22Dec2020 at 15:30 intramuscular in the left arm for COVID-19 immunisation; the patient was allergic to ranitidine hydrochloride (ZANTAC) and povidone iodine (BETADINE). Concomitant medications included gabapentin taken for an unspecified indication, start and stop date were not reported and ibuprofen, start and stop date were not reported, intermittent for headache. In Jan2021, the patient experienced new onset joint pain to distal joints (wrists, ankles), lasting almost 1 month since vaccination. Corrective treatments included OTC pain medication. The patient did not have COVID-19 prior to vaccination; the patient underwent nasal swab in Jan2021 with negative result. The patient had not recovered from the event.
